{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771355582,"nonce":"vC8G+GdJDKaVyxsq7x7wAtHXqmg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rsV5t","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/223","origin":"github"},"title":"worktree_create.sh --draft-pr targets GitHub default branch instead of .repos branch","message":"## Problem\n\n`worktree_create.sh --draft-pr` creates PRs targeting the **GitHub default branch** (e.g. `ros2`) instead of the branch specified in the `.repos` file (e.g. `jazzy`). This caused PR #26 in `rolker/ros2launch_gui` to target `ros2` when it should have targeted `jazzy`, resulting in merge conflicts against a completely different codebase.\n\n### Root cause\n\nTwo gaps in `worktree_create.sh`:\n\n1. **Draft PR targeting (lines ~640-647)**: `gh pr create` is called without `--base`, so GitHub defaults to its own default branch. For repos where the GitHub default (`ros2`) differs from the workspace-configured branch (`jazzy` per `underlay.repos`), the PR targets the wrong branch.\n\n2. **Branch creation (line ~405)**: `git worktree add -b \"$BRANCH_NAME\"` branches from whatever `HEAD` the local repo is on. This happened to be correct in practice (local was on `jazzy`), but it's not validated against the `.repos` file — it works by coincidence.\n\n### Impact\n\n- PRs show spurious merge conflicts against unrelated code\n- Manual intervention needed to retarget PRs and potentially rebase\n- Confusing for agents that assume \"default branch\" = GitHub default\n\n### Proposed fix\n\nWhen creating layer worktrees for a package, resolve the intended base branch from the `.repos` file:\n\n1. Search `*.repos` files under the workspace for the package's repo URL\n2. Extract the `version:` field as the canonical base branch\n3. Use it as the start point for `git worktree add -b` (instead of implicit HEAD)\n4. Pass `--base \u003cbranch\u003e` to `gh pr create --draft`\n\nIf the `.repos` lookup fails (package not found, multiple matches, etc.), fall back to current behavior and warn.\n\n### Workaround\n\nManually retarget the PR after creation:\n```bash\ngh api repos/\u003cowner\u003e/\u003crepo\u003e/pulls/\u003cN\u003e --method PATCH --field base=\u003ccorrect-branch\u003e\n```\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}